  "documents": [
    {
      "name": "Incident Response Playbook",
      "description": "Comprehensive incident response procedures and guidelines",
      "content": "# Incident Response Playbook\n\n## Overview\nThis playbook provides step-by-step procedures for responding to security incidents.\n\n## Incident Classification\n- **P1 - Critical**: Business critical systems compromised\n- **P2 - High**: Significant security breach with potential data loss\n- **P3 - Medium**: Security event requiring investigation\n- **P4 - Low**: Minor security anomaly\n\n## Response Procedures\n\n### Initial Response (0-30 minutes)\n1. Validate the incident\n2. Assess initial scope\n3. Activate response team\n4. Begin containment\n\n### Investigation (30 minutes - 2 hours)\n1. Collect forensic evidence\n2. Identify attack vectors\n3. Determine data exposure\n4. Document findings\n\n### Containment & Eradication (2-4 hours)\n1. Isolate affected systems\n2. Remove malicious artifacts\n3. Patch vulnerabilities\n4. Validate remediation\n\n### Recovery (4+ hours)\n1. Restore systems from backups\n2. Monitor for reinfection\n3. Implement additional controls\n4. Update security posture\n\n### Post-Incident (24-48 hours)\n1. Conduct lessons learned\n2. Update playbooks\n3. Report to stakeholders\n4. Improve defenses",
      "tags": [
        "incident-response",
        "playbook",
        "procedures"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "version": "2.0",
        "last_updated": "2025-01-15",
        "approved_by": "CISO"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Security Architecture Guidelines",
      "description": "Enterprise security architecture standards and best practices",
      "content": "# Security Architecture Guidelines\n\n## Defense in Depth Strategy\n\n### Network Security\n- Segmentation using VLANs and firewalls\n- Zero Trust Network Access (ZTNA)\n- Encrypted communications (TLS 1.3+)\n\n### Identity & Access Management\n- Multi-factor authentication (MFA)\n- Privileged access management (PAM)\n- Regular access reviews\n\n### Data Protection\n- Encryption at rest (AES-256)\n- Encryption in transit (TLS)\n- Data loss prevention (DLP)\n\n### Application Security\n- Secure SDLC practices\n- Regular vulnerability assessments\n- Web Application Firewall (WAF)\n\n### Cloud Security\n- Cloud Security Posture Management (CSPM)\n- Cloud Workload Protection (CWP)\n- Infrastructure as Code (IaC) scanning\n\n## Monitoring & Detection\n- SIEM correlation rules\n- User behavior analytics (UBA)\n- Threat hunting procedures\n- 24/7 SOC operations",
      "tags": [
        "architecture",
        "security-standards",
        "best-practices"
      ],
